real String theory is a theoretical framework in #meme physics that aims to reconcile general relativity and quantum mechanics, the two pillars of modern physics. At its core, string theory proposes that the fundamental building blocks of the universe are not point-like particles, but rather one-dimensional “strings” that vibrate at specific #breasts frequencies. These vibrations determine the properties of particles, such as mass and charge, much like the different notes produced by a vibrating guitar string 🎸. One of the most intriguing aspects of string theory is its requirement for additional #funny dimensions beyond the familiar three dimensions of space and one dimension of time. In fact, string theory suggests the existence of up to 11 dimensions! These extra dimensions are thought to be compactified or curled up so small that they are not easily observable #memes in our everyday experience 🌀. String theory has also given rise to the concept of #memer “branes,” multi-dimensional objects on which strings can attach. Our entire universe could be a 3-dimensional brane floating in a higher-dimensional space, with other branes potentially #humor hosting parallel universes 🪐. Despite its elegance and potential, string theory remains highly speculative. It has yet to produce testable predictions that can be experimentally #memedaily verified. Nonetheless, it offers a tantalizing glimpse into the deeper structure of reality and continues to inspire physicists in their quest for a unified theory of everything. Whether or not string theory ultimately proves correct, its #funnymemes influence on theoretical physics and the way we think about the universe is undeniable. 🌌✨

😭 Follow @g_oat for more A goat is a domesticated mammal belonging to the genus Capra, part of the family Bovidae. Known for their distinctive beards, upright horns, and agile climbing abilities, goats have been integral to human civilization for thousands of years. They were one of the first animals to be domesticated, with evidence suggesting this occurred around 10,000 years ago in the Near East. Goats are highly adaptable creatures, thriving in a wide range of environments, from rocky mountain slopes to arid deserts. They are herbivores, primarily grazing on grasses, shrubs, and leaves, but will also eat a variety of plant material, including some that other livestock might avoid. Their ability to browse on less-than-ideal forage has made them invaluable to people in areas where other animals might not be as productive. Social by nature, goats often live in herds, where they establish complex social structures. They are known for their curious and intelligent behavior, frequently interacting with their surroundings and even learning tasks when trained. Their vocalizations, which include bleats and baas, help maintain communication within the herd. In addition to their behavior, goats are important for various agricultural products. They provide milk, meat, and fiber (such as cashmere and mohair). Goat milk is highly nutritious and is used to make cheeses such as chèvre. In many cultures, goat meat, called chevon or mutton, is a popular source of protein. The fibers from certain breeds of goats, like the Angora goat, are harvested to make luxurious textiles. Overall, goats are versatile and resilient animals that have played a significant role in both rural economies and cultural practices worldwide. Their adaptability, intelligence, and wide range of uses continue to make them valuable companions to farmers and communities around the globe.

The look of Severance was just as important as the story itself, setting the tone for its eerie, almost hypnotic world. Jeremy Hindle and the production design team knew they had to get it just right, especially since so much of the show is just people walking through hallways—something that could easily feel dull without the right atmosphere. One of the most obsessive parts of that process was finding the perfect shade of white for Lumon’s offices. They tested around 50 different whites—some with hints of blue, green, red, or beige—laying them out and watching them through a projector for hours. In the end, only two worked, proving how much thought went into every tiny detail to make the world of Severance feel both ordinary and completely unnatural at the same time. #severance #appletv @appletv

😜🤘 when were memes invented The term "meme" was first introduced by Richard Dawkins, a British social scientist, in his book The Selfish Gene in 1976. Dawkins defined memes as cultural units that can spread from one individual to another. The word "meme" comes from the ancient Greek word mīmēma, which means "imitated". Dawkins uses this term to define the birth of culture with the assumption that culture is the formation of many replicators. Meanwhile, the first meme on the internet was the sideways smiley – 🙂 – which was created by Scott E. Fahlman, a US computer scientist, on September 19 1982. Memes became very popular when gags and rage comics adorned digital media platforms such as blogs, websites and social networking. #reels #fyp #memes

🔥 when were memes invented The term "meme" was first introduced by Richard Dawkins, a British social scientist, in his book The Selfish Gene in 1976. Dawkins defined memes as cultural units that can spread from one individual to another. The word "meme" comes from the ancient Greek word mīmēma, which means "imitated". Dawkins uses this term to define the birth of culture with the assumption that culture is the formation of many replicators. Meanwhile, the first meme on the internet was the sideways smiley – 🙂 – which was created by Scott E. Fahlman, a US computer scientist, on September 19 1982. Memes became very popular when gags and rage comics adorned digital media platforms such as blogs, websites and social networking. #reels #fyp #memes

Modern R&B (1990s-Present)
Sound: Blends R&B with hip-hop, electronic production, and pop influences.
✔ 1990s (Contemporary R&B) – Hip-hop beats, sleek production, and smooth vocals.
✔ 2000s (Hip-Hop Soul & Pop-R&B) – Strong hip-hop influences and mainstream appeal.
✔ 2010s-Present (Alternative R&B & Trap Soul) – Experimental production, electronic beats, and atmospheric soundscapes.
How to Identify Modern R&B:
• Electronic or trap-influenced beats (808s, synths, sampled loops).
• Auto-Tuned or highly polished vocal production (though still soulful).
• Blending of genres (hip-hop, pop, electronic, and alternative influences).
Artists:
• 1990s-2000s: Usher, Aaliyah, Destiny’s Child, R. Kelly
• 2010s-Present: The Weeknd, Frank Ocean, SZA, H.E.R., Summer Walker

Classic R&B vs. Modern R&B: A Breakdown

R&B has evolved significantly over the decades, blending with different genres while keeping its core focus on soulful vocals, groove, and emotional storytelling.


---

Classic R&B (1940s-1980s)

Sound: Influenced by blues, jazz, and gospel, often with live instrumentation (pianos, horns, guitars, drums).

✔ 1940s-1950s (Early R&B) – Rooted in blues and gospel.
✔ 1960s-1970s (Soul & Funk Influence) – More powerful vocals, funkier grooves.
✔ 1980s (Quiet Storm & New Jack Swing) – Smooth, romantic, and danceable styles emerge.

How to Identify Classic R&B:

Live instruments (real drums, pianos, brass, bass guitars).

Raw, emotional vocal delivery (often influenced by gospel).

Simple yet catchy grooves, sometimes incorporating jazz or funk.


Artists:

Ray Charles, Sam Cooke, Aretha Franklin (early R&B/soul)

Marvin Gaye, Stevie Wonder, Al Green (soul/funk R&B)

Prince, Luther Vandross, Whitney Houston (1980s smooth R&B)



---

Modern R&B (1990s
